node.text:
Homemade Halloween tapioca pearls from a couple of days ago.😁 Hooray!👻 I finally figured out 1) the slow-mo function on my phone, and 2) how to post it on IG!  Super lame self-congratulatory five!✋ Not the techiest person so tiny baby steps…😅 Besides Adobe Premiere, what do people use to make those professional-looking videos with cool captions, background music & special effects (e.g. stop-motion & doodles) for social media (e.g. IG Reels, YouTube, etc.), for non-Mac user??🤔 Your Auntie Melly wants to know!😅 
.
.

node.text:
Happy Qixi Festival (七夕 - sort of like a Chinese version of Valentine's Day)!❤️🎋 As with a lot of the traditional Chinese holidays, there is a somewhat bittersweet mythology behind it.🤓 In a nutshell, the mortal Niulang (牛郎 - the "cowherd", symbolising Altair, the brightest star in the constellation of Aquila) and the celestial Zhinü (織女 - the "weaver girl", symbolizing Vega, the brightest star in the constellation of Lyra) fell in love and got married.👫 The Heavenly Emperor (玉皇大帝, the head dude in heaven) found out about their union and was quite furious, so he sent his lackeys to bring Zhinü back to heaven.😱 The heartbroken Niulang chased after Zhinü but was deterred by the Queen Mother of the West (王母娘娘) who casted a Silver River (銀河, symbolising the Milky Way) to separate the lovers.😥 However, the sympathetic magpies (yes, the birds) formed a bridge for the lovers to cross.🐦 Deeply moved by the sight of love, the Heavenly Emperor allowed the lovers to meet on the Magpie Bridge once a year (gee, so generous of him!😑) on the seventh day of the seventh lunar month (aka Qixi Festival). The end!🤣 The gods in Chinese mythology are rather similar to that of Greek ones in the sense that they have very human qualities, including all the petty emotions…🙄
.
.

node.text:
💜, 💗, or 💙? These photos are as much about the plates as the macarons on them.😁  I’ve been collecting vintage cups and plates for about 15 years by now, and continue to be fascinated by the artistry and the history behind each piece.☕  Sometimes, on a flight of fancy, I’d sip on a cup of tea and wonder what it would be like to travel back in time.⏱️  Armed with knowledges from the future, would I be able to make considerable contributions for the betterment of humanity (let’s assume language wouldn’t pose an issue in this particular scenario)?🤔  Then, I’m reminded of how little I actually know about modern technology. I did not study science beyond high school (unless you count political science 🙄), so my understanding of how things work is rather rudimentary.😑  For example, I know the basic concept of electricity…but would I be able to actually invent an electric motor or a light bulb from scratch?💡 Would I be able to invent antibiotics to help cure the plague, cholera, or tuberculosis?💊 Even if I do somehow figured it out (perhaps by leaving some oranges out to mold?🤣), would I then be tried as a witch?!😱 Perhaps it's still best for me to stay put exactly where I am (where knowledge is readily available via the internet…🤣)
.
.
Yeti design inspired by the super talented @wildwhimsywoolies!
.
.

node.text:
The Internet tells me that today is Avocado Day 🥑, so here are some avo-cat-do-cuddle (try saying that 10 times fast) macarons to celebrate a fun but totally random food day!🤣 I must have been around 9 years old when I had my first avocado, as the fruit was not native to nor popular in Taiwan back then.  It was referred to as "butter fruit" (牛油果) and my mother cut it up (still rock hard, no one knew it needed ripening) and served it with soy sauce.  Needless to say, we all thought it was…objectionable.😣 Fast forward a couple decades and the world can't get enough of avocados.  According to British Vogue (an obvious authority on facts and figures 🙄), in the summer of 2017, more than 3 million photos of avocado toast were uploaded to Instagram every day!🍞 My relationship with avocados has also improved, evident by the fact that I now keep an avocado plant as a pet (see story highlights).😁 Will end this post with a fun fact - did you know that bay leaves, cinnamon and avocado are all part of the same Lauraceae (aka Laurel) family?😮 
.
.

node.text:
Christmas cookie cereals.🎄🍪  I first learnt about the whole “Christmas in July” concept back when I moved to Canada in the ‘90s.  Supposedly, it was first celebrated at a summer camp (i.e., Keystone Camp in Brevard, N.C.) in 1933, and subsequently popularised by the 1940 movie, “Christmas in July”.🤓  As someone who often struggles to be “seasonally appropriate” in both food (I crave stew at the height of summer, and icy treats when the weather is sub-zero) and fashion (I hang on to my sandals until first snow), I found the idea rather winsome if not random (which I’m also a big fan of, as evident by this post).🤣  Been taking things super slow this summer, which has done wonders for my neck, back, shoulders, arms & hips pains (I suspect this list will grow longer as I age).😑  With a milestone birthday looming in near distance (ugh!), I’ve been uncharacteristically self-reflective about this whole “aging gracefully” business.  Nothing profound to share as of yet, but paying more attention to my body seems to be a good place to start.😅 Grateful for any advice!❤️ 
.
.

node.text:
Here are some photos of the otter macarons made a couple weeks back that didn’t make the first cut (always a heart-wrenching exercise to select photos.😅 They are all my babies!!).🦦💙  I’ve been taking some time away from complicated bakes to reconnect with the physical world, now that Toronto has finally started to reopen after one of the longest covid lockdowns in the world (since last November).  I’m a bit of an introvert so didn’t really feel the monotony of the lockdown all that much (since I really do enjoy bumming around at home…perhaps a bit too much 😂), but it’s been so lovely seeing family and friends (not through an electronic screen), relaxing on a restaurant patio, and watching the city slowly coming back to life.❤️  There is definitely a sense of optimism in the air, albeit ever so cautious.🤞  How are things on your end?👀
.
.

node.text:
Canada Day beaver & moose macarons and pop-tarts.  Today marks the 154th anniversary of the Constitution Act of 1867, which established Canada as a country.🇨🇦  As a first generation immigrant, I will forever be grateful of the many privileges that come with being a Canadian.  Without diminishing the bravery of those who fought/fight for our country and the hardworks of everyday folks who keep our economy and infrastructures afloat, this is also a solemn day of reflection to recognise and correct our country's past and current mistreatments of the Indigenous Peoples in Canada.  May we, as a nation, learn from the past and do better tomorrow.🧡
.
.

node.text:
🐻 & 🐰 tea party, to usher in a brand new week (7 photos in total, because I'm having the hardest time choosing)!💕  The bear and bunny were the earliest designs I've done in macarons, so I figured it only made sense for me to use them for my first proper deco cake roll (for my not-so-little-anymore buddy who just turned 11 years old 🎉). I had originally drawn a much more complicated design, but wisely decided that I should probably learn to walk before attempting to run.😅  The cake roll was filled with mascarpone cream (flavoured with freeze-dried strawberry powder) and whole fresh strawberries.🍓  In addition to the macarons and cake roll, I've also made some bear-shaped sugar cubes (also strawberry flavoured) to go with the tea.  Gotta love the tiny pretty things in life!😁
.
.
I'm very grateful to @keempossible_2 for teaching me how to make deco cake rolls.❤️
.
.
Sugar cube mold designed by & purchased from @cochat620.
.
.

node.text:
Sailor Moon themed treats (Luna and Artemis macarons in photo 1, transformation brooch cookies in photo 2) done for a pop-up cosplay café about 5 years ago.💖 Thought about these treats since I "attempted" to watch the newly released Sailor Moon Eternal: The Movie on Netflix this week. I had enjoyed watching the original Sailor Moon anime series on YTV back in the '90s, but for some reason find the new movie somewhat…cringey.😅 Has Chibiusa always had such a serious case of Oedipus complex?!🙄 The movie is obviously still hyper fluffy and pink…which is a bit much in my current state of, umm, oldness.🤣 Did anyone else watch Sailor Moon growing up?  What do you think about the new movie?!🤔
.
.

node.text:
Love is love.❤️ Celebrating Pride Month with this colourful take on the hurricane Swiss roll trend that was popular a couple of years ago.😋 What I love about this pattern is that no two slices are the same!🌈 The cake is filled with stabilised whipped cream and strawberry milk jelly hearts (which I failed to center…but can't muster up enough willpower to redo).😅🍓 
.
.
I'm very grateful to @keempossible_2 for sharing with me her delicious cake recipe and many helpful tips!🙏
.
.

node.text:
Panda high tea with my favourite French, Japanese and Taiwanese desserts - macarons, dango (rice dumplings) served with kinako (roasted soy bean powder), and pineapple cakes.🐼🍵 I haven't had a chance to make cute things lately, which doesn't mean that I haven't been busy making stuff.😅 On the contrary, I've never spent more time in the kitchen than in the last 3 weeks or so.😁 Have been challenging myself to learn new things…which resulted in a lot of, umm, ugly but delicious things (that all went into my tummy).🤣 I thought I would be discouraged since I'm a bit of a perfectionist, but it's actually been rather invigorating.❤️ Hopefully will have something prettier to share with you soon.😆 Will probably need to start exercising to shed all that dessert weight.😑 Not sure about you, but I've certainly became softer around the edges (literally fluffy) during th pandemic…😶
.
.

node.text:
Puppies!!!🐶 This was a special batch of macarons done for my friend, inspired by her then-puppy Labrador retriever, Storm (3 photos). Since then, Storm was joined by her adorable human little sister, and very soon a little brother.❤️ Sometimes the wheel of time turns so fast it makes my head spin.😥 Hope everyone is having a great week so far, almost the weekend!😀
.
.
